The paper presents a visualization method for eye-tracking data analysis, which is a common topic in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and computer vision (cs.CV) research. The use of clustering algorithms and similarity matrices also suggests a potential fit for natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) applications. Finally, the paper discusses limitations and scalability issues, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) research.
